author: cbs8
title: Amber Alert canceled, Lincoln Parish boy is found safe
text:
RUSTON, La. (AP) - State police have canceled an Amber Alert issued for an 8-year-old Lincoln Parish boy.
Troopers say Dakota Knox was found in Ouachita Parish late Sunday night. They have not released any details about where Knox was found.
Police says they are still looking for 23-year-old Sommer Ann Hattaway, who allegedly abducted Knox when she stole the car in which the boy was sleeping early Sunday morning.
Police have not said whether the vehicle, a black 2000 Mercury Mountaineer, had been found.
The SUV was parked at the Lincoln Motel in Ruston when it was stolen.
